items.title: US stocks close flat as Nasdaq extends weekly gains, S&P 500 and Dow dip
items.description: The Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 86.06 points, or 0.20%, to 43,828.06, the S&P 500 lost 0.16 point, or 0.00%, to 6,051.09 and the Nasdaq Composite gained 23.88 points, or 0.12%, to 19,926.72.

items.title: Market extends gain in fourth week; IT, telecom, realty stocks shine
items.description: During the week, Foreign Institutional Investors (FIIs) sold equities worth Rs 226.70 crore, while Domestic Institutional Investors (DII) bought equities worth Rs 2880.02 crore.

items.title: Broader indices underperform but these smallcaps gain between 10-37%
items.description: On the sectoral front, BSE Information Technology index rose 2.6 percent, BSE Telecom index was up 1.7 percent, BSE Realty index rose 0.6 percent. On the other hand, BSE Energy and FMCG indices shed 1.5 percent each, and BSE Oil & Gas index slipped nearly 1 percent.
